article.headline: Utah State 69, Louisiana Tech 49
article.story: LOGAN, Utah (AP) -- Jaycee Carroll scored 27 points in Utah State's 69-49 win over Louisiana Tech Saturday. Carroll scored on 9-for-15 shooting for the Aggies (12-5, 1-2). He also led the team in assists and rebounds. Durrall Peterson also scored 11 in the Aggies' first Western Athletic Conference win this season. The Bulldogs (4-12, 2-2) were led in scoring by Chad McKenzie with 13, Trey McDowell with 11 and Harry Disy with 10. The Bulldogs took the lead 43-42 six minutes into the second half on a 3-point shot by Drew Washington. USU then went on a 19-2 run, sparked by a four-point play by Peterson, and led 61-45 with 5:15 to play. The Bulldog's leading scorer, McKenzie (13.3 ppg) played much of the second half in foul trouble, picking up his fourth personal foul with 16:20 to play. He fouled out with 3:12 left in the game. The teams tied or traded leads 10 times in a close first half. An aggressive defense by the Bulldogs resulted in 12 fouls being called in the half, with USU gaining 10 points on free throws. USU's largest lead of the first half was just before the buzzer sounded when Carroll made a put-back basket and free throw to give the Aggies a 37-32 halftime edge.
